RACE.RACE_TEXT: PENN NATIONAL RACE 1 1M 70Y Dirt CR: 87. Claiming Purse 18100. (PLUS UP TO 40% PABF) FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE MAY 10 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 123 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since October 10 Allowed 2 lbs. Such A Race Since September 10 Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $16,000, if for $14,000, allowed 2 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $12,500 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: NICK PAPAGIORGIO was away alertly and got over towards the inside into the first turn, then was well rated along the inside, shifted off the rail leaving the five sixteenths pole, came three wide into the lane and shifted out to make an outside bid on the lane and edged away late to prove best under a drive. ROMP was off a bit slowly, then shifted out and tracked the pace three wide on the first turn, made a three wide bid leaving the five sixteenths and gained a short advantage heading to the quarter pole, then was clear by the furlong marker but collared by the winner nearing the sixteenth marker and could not go with that rival late, second best. SOUPER ROYAL MOON set a pressured pace along the inside and was headed by the five sixteenths and gave way grudgingly, bested rest. YOUNGEST OF FIVE was three wide into the first turn, pressed the pace two wide and made a bid between rivals on the far turn but flattened out the final furlong. SUPER DUDE was in tight on the inside into the first turn, then shifted out leaving the five eighths marker and had a four wide pursuit leaving the half mile marker and had no rally.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: PENN NATIONAL RACE 4 1M 70Y Dirt CR: 91. Allowance Purse 28000. (PLUS UP TO 40% PABF) FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON A RACE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, OR PENNSYLVANIA BRED. Three Year Olds, 123 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since October 10 Allowed 2 lbs. Such A Race Since September 10 Allowed 4 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $16,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: JUMP FOR THE WIN set the pace on the inside, then was pressured on the backstretch, dueled by the quarter pole with THUNDERLAN, then had a long drive with that rival, came out slightly under left hand crop and exchanged bumps but held on determinedly to prove best. THUNDERIAN stalked the early pace three wide, then made a bid to duel with the winner two wide on the far turn, then exchanged bumps through the stretch drive but hung late. STEADY JOHN had an awkward break, settled early, advanced on the inside on the far turn, then made a inside bid in the lane but needed more late. GOOSE HUNTER chased the early pace four wide, shifted in to the inside at the nine sixteenths, then dropped back on the inside, then made a inside move nearing the quarter pole and had some late kick. CAJUN OCCASION tracked the pace three to four wide and weakened in the lane. The rider on number two THUNDERLAN filed an OBJECTION against the winner for interference in the stretch, after the STEWARDS reviewed the video replays the OBJECTION was not allowed and the race was left as is.

ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked pace 3 wide, bid 2 wide, dueled, exchanged bumps,hung
